1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6
{ Bg7 is of course playable but then Black can't play 'Gurgenidze System' in the Maroczy Bind which is part of this repertoire. }
5. Nxc6 bxc6 6. Qd4
{ This isn't something Black should be afraid of even though it may look scary. In general one shouldn't attack with the Queen alone in the opening as we all know. }
6... Nf6 7. e5 Nd5 8. e6 f6 9. exd7+ Bxd7
{ The position looks a bit odd but Black has much better development. } 10. Bc4
e5 { Kicking White's Queen and gaining useful tempo. } 11. Qh4 Bg7 12. O-O Be6
13. Nc3 O-O 14. Rd1 Qc7
{ Black is better developed and has great control in the center. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
