[White "Road To The Main Line"]
[Black "Road To The Main Line #2"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6
{ Bg7 is of course playable but then Black can't play 'Gurgenidze System' in the Maroczy Bind which is part of this repertoire. }
5. Nc3 Bg7 6. Nde2 Nf6 7. g3
{ This is quite respectable way to meet the Dragon but this seems to be too slow against the Accelerated Dragon ! }
7... b5
{ Normally Black would have to play ...Rb8 first when White can always go a4 but here Black strikes first using the fact Nxb5 would drop the central pawn on e4. }
8. Bg2 Rb8 9. O-O O-O 10. h3 { preventing .. . Ng4 and preparing Be3 } 10... d6
11. Be3 b4 12. Nd5 Nd7
{ Attacking b2 pawn immediately. Black has great play on the queenside. He can play ...Qa5, ...Ba6 next or even ...Nde5 trying to occupy c4 is worth consideration. }
*

