[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6
{ Bg7 is of course playable but then Black can't play 'Gurgenidze System' in the Maroczy Bind which is part of this repertoire. }
5. Nc3 Bg7 6. Nb3 { This doesn't look too ambitious. } 6... Nf6
{ Bxc3 is a very interesting alternative, but let's stick to the simple plan. }
7. Be2 O-O 8. Be3 a5 9. a4 Nb4 10. f4
{ Dubious is 10. e5 as after Ne8 11. f4 d6 White's center collapsed and Black took over in J.Tomczak - P.Nguyen, Zgierz  (rapid)  2018. }
10... d6 { d5 is playable but the text is more solid. } 11. O-O Be6
{ Bd7 is a decent alternative. } 12. Nd4 Qc8
{ Allowing White to grab a Bishop pair but Black is very active to compensate for that. }
13. Nxe6 Qxe6 { As the pawn hangs on e4 everyone plays } 14. Bf3
{ stronger is 14. Bf2N with balanced play  but here comes } 14... Nxe4 15. Nxe4
d5 { with a clear advantage in P.Moran - A.Frois, Linares 1995 } *

