12... Nf6 13. O-O-O O-O 14. Qc4+ Kh8 15. Be2 d6 16. Qxc6
{ Black is happy to give such pawn as open lines against White's King are more important. }
16... Rb8 17. Bd4 Qb4
{ D.Szoen - A.Fedorov, Warsaw 2005. Black has great compensation. White's position is very unplesant. }
