[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6
{ Bg7 is of course playable but then Black can't play 'Gurgenidze System' in the Maroczy Bind which is part of this repertoire. }
5. Nc3 Bg7 6. Be3 Nf6 7. Bc4 O-O 8. Bb3
{ The Main Line and only way for White to fight for the initiative. } 8... d6
9. f3 Bd7 10. Qd2 Nxd4 11. Bxd4 b5 12. a4 b4
{ bxa4 is not as good in my view because White hasn't commited his King to the queenside yet and he didn't even push h4 so he will castle kingside and hammer down the a file with advantage. }
13. Nd5 Nxd5 14. Bxg7 Kxg7 15. exd5 a5
{ Qb6 is mentioned by Negi as "the key to Black's revival" and probably the reason he wrote additional chapter on 10. h4. I agree this is fine but I want to show a bit different way which I like. }
16. h4 f6
{ a Novelty. 16. ..e5 is safest according to Gawain Jones but I'm not so sure. In my view f6 even though it looks ugly it's actually very solid. }
17. h5 g5 18. h6+ Kh8
{ White's attack is going nowhere and his Bishop is out of play. Black is not worse at all in my opinion. }
