[White "Maroczy Bind - Gurgenidze System"]
[Black "Maroczy Bind - Gurgenidze System #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6
{ Bg7 is of course playable but then Black can't play 'Gurgenidze System' in the Maroczy Bind which is part of this repertoire. }
5. c4
{ Entering so called Maroczy Bind setup which isn't possible in traditional Dragon but we have to learn it. This is the price we pay for choosing this move order. }
5... Nf6 6. Nc3 d6 7. Nc2
{ Avoiding any exchanges but loosing some time thus I think Black should be quick with his play. Otherwise he'll be left with very passive position. }
7... Bg7 8. Be2 O-O 9. O-O Be6
{ Nfd7 is the main move but I'd like to suggest a bit different line. } 10. Be3
Nd7 11. Qd2 Qa5
{ is just good for Black. To avoid ...Bxc3 ideas White can play } 12. Nd4
{ but then } 12... Nxd4 { exchanging one pair of Knights is good for Black }
13. Bxd4 Bxd4
{ and also exchanging dark squared Bishop is good for Black unless Black's King is under some pressure but here it is not and after }
14. Qxd4 Qc5 { Black has good control over dark squares. } *

