{ Be6 with ...Qa5 is the main line but I believe the line I recommend here is easier to learn and it is by no means worse in my opinion. }
11. O-O a4 12. f3
{ This isn't forced but White needs this move at some point if he wants to jump with his Knight and sometimes it is useful to prevent ...Ng4. }
12... Qa5 13. Rab1 Be6 14. Rfc1 Rfc8 15. b4 axb3 16. axb3 Qb4
{ Usually it is not the best idea to block pawns with the most powerful piece as it can easily be driven away but here I do not see how White can do that. I don't see also how White can regroup effectively while Black's Queen puts some pressure and that is something really annoying. }
