[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6
{ Bg7 is of course playable but then Black can't play 'Gurgenidze System' in the Maroczy Bind which is part of this repertoire. }
5. c4
{ Entering so called Maroczy Bind setup which isn't possible in traditional Dragon but we have to learn it. This is the price we pay for choosing this move order. }
5... Nf6 6. Nc3 d6 7. Be2 { Of course 7. Be3 would be innacurate due to Ng4. }
7... Nxd4 { Black is happy to exchange some pieces as he has less space. } 8.
Qxd4 Bg7 9. Be3 O-O 10. Qd2 a5
{ Be6 with ...Qa5 is the main line but I believe the line I recommend here is easier to learn and it is by no means worse in my opinion. }
11. f3 a4 12. Rc1
{ 12. Rb1 Qa5 13. Nd5 Nxd5 14. exd5 e6 ! was equal in M.Brancaleoni - P.Nguyen, Gabicce Mare 2018 but as I proved in that game Black can still play for a full point. This will be covered in a bonus video. }
12... Qa5 13. Rc2
{ A tricky move delaying castle as the King will be useful in the center once we exchange Queens. For 13.O-O see 11.O-O. }
13... Be6 14. Nd5 Nxd5 15. cxd5 Rfc8 16. Qxa5 Rxa5 17. Kd2 Rxc2+ 18. Kxc2 Bd7
19. Rc1 e6
{ Y. Gruenfeld - O.Aharon, Jerusalem 2014. A draw is the most likely outcome but still both sides can play a bit. }
