1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Qxd4
{ This wouldn't be possible if Black chooses Nc6 move order but then he would have to learn 3. Bb5 Rossolimo. }
4... Nf6 5. Nc3
{ For couple years I was struggling to find a satisfactory way to meet this system but finally I managed to do so and I will present a nice Novelty. }
5... Nc6 6. Qa4 d6 7. e5 dxe5
{ The main move. Ng4 !? is an alternative but to my knowledge White has chances for slight edge there. }
