6... Qc7 7. Bxa7 { I was a bit shocked when I saw it for the first time. } 7...
Nc6 { Of course not Rxa7 ?? as 8. Qd4 would pick up one of the Rooks ! } 8. Be3
Bg7 9. Nf3 Nf6 10. Be2 O-O 11. O-O
{ White is a pawn up but Black has some lead in development plus the pawn which is gone wasn't so important. }
11... Ng4
{ Black has to do something before White completes his development and this is the way to go. }
